be)\n  | publisher=SMC Publishing | place=\n  | isbn=957-638-599-7\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n}}\n* {{citation\n  | last=Pan | first=Ying\n  | year=1996\n  | title=Taiwan pingpu zu shi (History of Taiwan's Pingpu Tribes)\n  | publisher=SMC Publishing | place=Taipei\n  | isbn=957-638-358-7\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n}}\n* Interview: 2003: Pan Jin Yu (age 93) -in Puli\n* {{citation\n  | last=Phillips | first=Steven\n  | year=2003\n  | title=Between Assimilation and Independence:The Taiwanese Encounter Nationalist China, 1945-1950\n  | publisher=Stanford University Press | place=Stanford California\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n}}\n* {{citation\n  | last=Pickering | first=W.A. |authorlink=William A. Pickering\n  | year=1898\n  | title=Pioneering In Formosa\n  | publisher=Hurst and Blackett | place=London\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n  |ol=7204709M |url=https://archive.org/details/pioneeringinform00pickrich \n  }} Republished 1993, Taipei, SMC Publishing. {{ISBN|957-638-163-0}}.\n* Reuters, \"Taiwan election shooting suspect dead,\" (2005)|reference=Reuters. ''[http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200503/s1318054.htm \"Taiwan election shooting suspect dead,\" 7 March 2005]''.\n* {{citation\n  | last=Rubinstein | first=Murray A.\n  | year=1999\n  | title=Taiwan: A New History\n  | publisher=M.E. Sharpe, Inc | place=New York\n  | isbn=1-56324-816-6\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n}}\n* {{citation\n  | last=Shepherd | first=John Robert\n  | year=1995\n  | title=Marriage and Mandatory Abortion among the 17th Century Siraya\n  | publisher= | place=Arlington VA\n  | postscript=.\n  | ref=none\n}}\n* {{citation| last=Simon| first=Scott| date=4 January 2006| title=Formosa's First Nations and the Japanese: from Colonial Rule to Postcolonial Resistance| url=http://japanfocus.org/products/details/1565| journal=Japan Focus| postscript=.| ref=none| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313182115/http://japanfocus.org/products/details/1565| 